{
  "text": "Damage to membrane lipids by ROS such as peroxide, superoxide anion, hydroxyl radical, and singlet oxygen may ultimately lead to inflammation [CITATION_1] . Although there is a strong association between chronic inflammation and cancer, investigators have not yet uncovered all the molecules, pathways, and mechanisms involved, and there are numerous questions regarding the mechanisms and targets of pro-inflammatory mediators of tumor development [CITATION_2] .",
